The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Monday, May 31, 2004  LOOSE CHANGE
																								HDFC Mutual Fund has decided to reconstitute the HDFC Cash Management Fund  Investment Plan, an ultra short-term debt fund. With effect from June 23, 2004, the dividend option under the above plan would be discontinued. The growth option will be renamed as HDFC Cash Management Fund - Savings Plus Plan. At present, both the growth and dividend options under the existing fund have separate portfolios. However, after restructuring, Savings Plus Plan will offer a dividend option which will have a common portfolio with the growth option. 																								Benchmark Mutual Fund has launched four plans under a fund of funds scheme, which will invest in exchange traded funds. The four plans are Junior BeES, Nifty BeES, Nifty 100  a blend of Nifty BeES and Junior BeES and Nifty 100 Balance  a blend of Nifty BeES, Junior BeES and Liquid BeES. The minimum investment amount is Rs 10,000 and offer both growth and dividend options. The initial public offer will remain open from May 27 to June 22, 2004. 																								The launch of Sundaram India Leadership Fund has been rescheduled for May 31. The offer will remain open till June 18. The launch was earlier postponed owing to the uncertain political situation and volatility on bourses.
